WEBVTT

00:41.833 --> 00:44.500
-[birds chirping]
-[wind rustling leaves]

00:55.875 --> 00:59.125
["If It Don't Twang" by Paul Pace
playing over car radio]

01:03.416 --> 01:04.458
[truck switches off]

01:10.250 --> 01:13.000
[quacking ringtone playing]

01:15.291 --> 01:16.208
[scoffs]

01:17.500 --> 01:19.458
-Yo! [scoffs]
-[boy on phone] Listen to this.

01:19.541 --> 01:23.083
Amber told Stacy she was down to do
some nasty shit with you after the game.

01:23.166 --> 01:26.416
Macon, slow down, slow down.
Wait. Okay, which one is she?

01:26.500 --> 01:28.750
[Macon]
You met her a hundred times. A-hole.

01:28.833 --> 01:33.625
Hogwarts? [chuckles]
No, no, fuck that. You'd have to pay me.

01:33.708 --> 01:36.083
[Macon] What? Pay you?
She's throwing herself at you!

01:36.166 --> 01:38.291
No, I'm serious.
Not even for, like, a million--

01:38.375 --> 01:41.750
[Macon] We really can't all be
flat-chested and pissed off like Hailey.

01:41.833 --> 01:44.375
Maybe, just maybe you should
lower your standards once in a while.

01:44.458 --> 01:46.500
Um, Macon, hold up one second?

01:46.583 --> 01:47.916
[timer ticking]

01:48.500 --> 01:49.416
Mom?

01:51.041 --> 01:52.125
Sadie?

01:56.708 --> 01:59.333
-I don't know. It's nothing.
-[Macon] I thought they were gone.

01:59.416 --> 02:01.416
Yeah, they said
they were tailgating before.

02:01.500 --> 02:02.458
[gagging]

02:02.541 --> 02:04.875
The fuck!

02:04.958 --> 02:07.958
I swear. My sister is licking
the powder off the Doritos

02:08.041 --> 02:13.083
and putting them back in the bag.
Fucking body dysmorphia at age eight.

02:13.166 --> 02:16.416
[Macon] She is a weird kid.
And I was a weird kid.

02:16.500 --> 02:19.166
[ticking grows louder]

02:19.250 --> 02:20.916
I'm just gonna crash before--

02:21.000 --> 02:23.750
-[Macon] Little stress relief!
-Dude, I don't pregame that way.

02:23.833 --> 02:26.583
[Macon] Relax!
Why are you so serious right now?

02:26.666 --> 02:28.958
'Cause it's like pure protein.

02:29.041 --> 02:31.416
Why would I want good protein
out of my body before--

02:31.500 --> 02:34.000
[Macon] All right, but do not oversleep.

02:34.083 --> 02:36.708
Yeah, I'll be there.
Kickoff's in like four hours.

02:36.791 --> 02:39.041
[Macon] Well, I'm gonna go
lose protein for four hours.

02:39.125 --> 02:42.500
[chuckling] Okay, yeah.
Have fun pregaming, perv.

02:44.291 --> 02:45.375
[phone chimes]

02:51.166 --> 02:52.083
[sighs]

02:52.875 --> 02:54.500
[timer ticking continues]

03:03.333 --> 03:06.750
[alarm ringing]

03:10.875 --> 03:13.208
[ominous music playing]

03:16.166 --> 03:17.750
The fuck?

03:22.416 --> 03:24.000
[panting]

03:26.041 --> 03:27.041
[door slams]

03:28.000 --> 03:30.291
[suspenseful music playing]

03:48.291 --> 03:50.083
Fuckin' truck.

03:58.916 --> 04:00.125
[door locks]

04:00.208 --> 04:02.416
[ominous electronic music playing]

04:05.500 --> 04:06.416
[phone dialing]

04:07.583 --> 04:10.208
-[exhales deeply]
-[line ringing]

04:13.458 --> 04:15.500
[operator] 911, what's your emergency?

04:16.958 --> 04:18.708
-Hello, this is--
-[phone beeps off]

04:24.708 --> 04:25.958
[phone ringing]

04:40.375 --> 04:42.791
-[girl] You've reached the Pace residence.
-Shit!

04:42.875 --> 04:45.000
-Leave a message after the beep.
-[machine beeps]

04:48.291 --> 04:50.333
[phone ringing]

04:58.666 --> 05:00.291
[panting]

05:00.375 --> 05:02.416
[suspenseful music playing]

05:19.916 --> 05:21.458
[breathing shakily]

05:22.625 --> 05:24.000
[quacking ringtone playing]

05:35.666 --> 05:37.375
Whatever little game this is,

05:39.041 --> 05:40.833
whatever you think you know,

05:42.083 --> 05:43.333
you don't know shit!

05:48.708 --> 05:50.416
[inhales deeply]

05:55.625 --> 05:56.541
[sighs]

05:58.333 --> 05:59.583
[exhales shakily]

06:08.166 --> 06:09.666
[clattering]

06:13.791 --> 06:15.000
[yells]

06:17.000 --> 06:18.791
[panting]

06:19.666 --> 06:20.916
You're in my house,

06:21.500 --> 06:23.541
so I can legally kill you,

06:24.333 --> 06:25.708
you fuck!

06:26.708 --> 06:27.541
Come out!

06:28.500 --> 06:29.541
[screaming]

06:29.625 --> 06:31.458
[crying]

06:31.541 --> 06:33.000
[gasping]

06:33.666 --> 06:36.208
[spluttering]

06:36.291 --> 06:39.541
You want money?
Because I can Venmo you right now.

06:39.625 --> 06:41.833
Like, no one's gotta know.

06:41.916 --> 06:44.375
Hey, hey, hey.
Look, man, we-- We were all wasted.

06:44.458 --> 06:46.416
It was…
It was just, like, a team bonding thing.

06:46.500 --> 06:48.416
Like… like, I swear.

06:48.500 --> 06:51.333
This isn't who I am! This isn't

06:52.333 --> 06:53.416
me?

06:54.958 --> 06:56.750
[grunting]

07:04.208 --> 07:05.958
[quacking ringtone playing]

07:14.333 --> 07:16.333
-[crowd chattering]
-Pick up the phone, son.

07:16.416 --> 07:17.416
[player] Hike!

07:18.541 --> 07:19.541
Goddamn it.

07:20.125 --> 07:21.333
[grunts]

07:21.416 --> 07:24.333
[announcer] Fumble in the backfield!
Defense recovered!

07:24.416 --> 07:26.708
-[crowd cheering]
-[announcer] First down, Wampus Cats!

07:26.791 --> 07:30.250
[cheerleaders] Hiss and scratch!
We're Wampus Cats!

07:30.333 --> 07:32.291
I'm sure he'll turn up. It's not like him.

07:34.041 --> 07:35.958
[announcer] Caleb Greeley
receives the handoff!

07:36.958 --> 07:39.166
-Caleb out in the open!
-[phone chiming]

07:39.250 --> 07:40.666
He's gonna go!

07:40.750 --> 07:42.458
[phones chiming]

07:43.041 --> 07:43.916
[gasping]

07:44.000 --> 07:45.041
[panting]

07:45.125 --> 07:46.250
[phone chimes]

07:46.333 --> 07:48.958
[boy in video] Jackson, Jackson,
get off him! Get off him!

07:49.833 --> 07:51.125
[panting] Whoo!

07:52.791 --> 07:54.208
[boy in video] Caleb, you okay, man?

07:54.291 --> 07:55.791
Come on, man. You all right?

07:56.291 --> 07:58.041
[laughs, panting]

08:00.750 --> 08:03.083
[ominous electronic music playing]

08:09.083 --> 08:10.500
[girl 1] Did you hear about Jackson?

08:10.583 --> 08:12.583
-[boy 1] So fucked up.
-[girl 2] Terrifying.

08:12.666 --> 08:14.666
-[girl 1] Who would do this?
-[girl 3] You saw that video.

08:14.750 --> 08:16.750
[girl 4] Jackson was out of line.

08:16.833 --> 08:19.416
[boy 2] So he beat someone up.
Doesn't mean he had to die.

08:19.500 --> 08:21.541
[girl 1]
That was way more than hazing, though.

08:21.625 --> 08:23.916
-[girl 5] It was brutal.
-[girl 6] He targeted Caleb.

08:24.000 --> 08:25.458
[girl 1] Is it 'cause Caleb's gay?

08:25.541 --> 08:27.500
[boy 3] Probably jealous
Caleb's the better player.

08:27.583 --> 08:29.333
[boy 2] Caleb never even reported it.

08:29.416 --> 08:30.875
[girl 6] So who told?

08:30.958 --> 08:32.666
[boy 2] The whole team was there.

08:32.750 --> 08:34.416
[boy 4] They think Caleb's behind it.

08:35.000 --> 08:36.875
-[girl 7 scoffs] What?
-[boy 2] He was in the game.

08:36.958 --> 08:39.458
-[girl 8] He could've hired a killer.
-[phone ringing]

08:40.125 --> 08:41.708
[girl 9] Everyone got the video.

08:41.791 --> 08:43.875
-Everyone.
-[girl 10] The whole town.

08:44.875 --> 08:47.333
-[boy 5] To make a point.
-[girl 11] What point?

08:47.416 --> 08:48.416
[girl 12] Who knows?

08:48.916 --> 08:52.333
-[girl 13] I'm honestly scared.
-[boy 5] What do we do? Go back to school?

08:52.416 --> 08:54.833
-[girl 14] I can't sleep.
-[boy 5] I can't live here anymore.

08:54.916 --> 08:57.250
-[girl 15] The sheriff have a suspect?
-[boy 5] He won't say.

08:57.333 --> 08:58.708
[girl 16] So sad, though.

08:58.791 --> 09:00.666
[girl 17] What if it happens again?

09:08.083 --> 09:09.708
[indistinct chattering]

09:32.916 --> 09:34.291
[girl snickering]

09:37.791 --> 09:38.625
What?

09:39.375 --> 09:41.458
Store ran out of all the sad cards.

09:41.541 --> 09:45.250
Did I say anything? I think it's great,
really. I love that optimism.

09:45.333 --> 09:46.875
At least she got him something.

09:46.958 --> 09:48.375
Sorry I don't know what to get a guy

09:48.458 --> 09:50.458
who beat the shit out of me
for fun for three years.

09:50.541 --> 09:51.416
Hmm.

09:53.291 --> 09:55.083
-Really?
-Wow.

09:55.833 --> 09:57.250
Built-in immunity. [laughs]

09:57.333 --> 09:59.208
No teacher's gonna punish
the grief-stricken.

09:59.291 --> 10:00.791
Oh, that's actually pretty smart.

10:00.875 --> 10:03.416
Am I crazy, or are people
side-eyeing me right now?

10:03.500 --> 10:05.541
-You're never crazy, babe.
-[sighs]

10:05.625 --> 10:09.041
Caleb's getting it worse.
Fucked up they're blaming him.

10:09.125 --> 10:10.875
Of course they blame the gay guy.

10:11.625 --> 10:12.833
[Macon] Last Friday night,

10:14.791 --> 10:17.416
Jackson Pace
took a knee on the field of life.

10:18.333 --> 10:21.208
But damn if he didn't live every day
like it was the fourth quarter.

10:21.916 --> 10:23.333
I'll never forget you, son.

10:24.666 --> 10:25.833
♪ In the mist ♪

10:26.708 --> 10:28.208
♪ There was a purr… ♪

10:28.291 --> 10:29.250
Oh no.

10:29.333 --> 10:32.541
[Macon]
♪ And when that purr turned to a grr ♪

10:33.125 --> 10:36.333
♪ Six legs walked into the light ♪

10:36.916 --> 10:39.916
♪ And we knew it was time to fight ♪

10:40.000 --> 10:44.125
-Actually, he's not half bad.
-[students] ♪ So go, Cats, go ♪

10:44.750 --> 10:48.333
♪ To victory ♪

10:48.416 --> 10:52.166
♪ To God, his game ♪

10:52.250 --> 10:56.375
♪ And his glory! ♪

10:58.500 --> 11:01.000
Hope they're serving Fireball
up in paradise, brother.

11:02.333 --> 11:03.458
Now I wanna die.

11:04.958 --> 11:07.708
[Macon] One time
we were having pizza, right?

11:07.791 --> 11:10.875
And I was telling him
I was having trouble finding Stacy's clit.

11:11.375 --> 11:12.875
Jackson goes with the pizza box,

11:12.958 --> 11:15.666
makes a diagram with pizza sauce
to show me where it was on her body.

11:15.750 --> 11:18.000
[boy snickers] Classic Jackson.

11:18.750 --> 11:20.250
I'm literally right here.

11:21.833 --> 11:24.541
I got a prime suspect. Macon Bewley.

11:26.125 --> 11:29.541
Well, he's too dumb
not to get caught, so win-win.

11:29.625 --> 11:30.916
[giggles]

11:31.000 --> 11:31.875
[chuckling]

11:32.541 --> 11:35.041
Alternate theory. My dad.

11:35.125 --> 11:36.666
Ah, you wish.

11:36.750 --> 11:37.958
Think about it.

11:38.041 --> 11:40.500
No way Jackson's parents
wanna live in that house

11:40.583 --> 11:43.333
on that farm
where their… where their kid was killed

11:43.416 --> 11:45.166
any longer than they have to, right?

11:45.250 --> 11:47.833
Who else wants that farm
more than Skipper Sandford,

11:47.916 --> 11:49.958
the land baron of Osborne?

11:50.041 --> 11:52.708
-"Chaos breeds opportunity, boy."
-[girl 1 laughs]

11:52.791 --> 11:56.083
[boy] "And this is an opportunity
for Sandford Family Farms."

11:56.166 --> 11:58.166
[students laughing]

11:58.250 --> 11:59.750
[student] You can sit with us.

12:05.250 --> 12:06.166
Uh.

12:06.708 --> 12:08.125
Sorry. Thanks.

12:08.708 --> 12:09.541
I'm Darby.

12:09.625 --> 12:11.916
I know. I'm Caleb.

12:12.833 --> 12:15.541
A pleasure to meet y'all,
I guess, officially.

12:17.125 --> 12:18.083
Caleb.

12:18.583 --> 12:20.166
It's not a country club, Caleb.

12:20.708 --> 12:21.541
I'm Makani.

12:22.625 --> 12:24.208
That's Rodrigo,

12:24.291 --> 12:25.458
Zach,

12:25.541 --> 12:27.500
and Alex. She's our bitch-in-residence.

12:27.583 --> 12:29.625
-Oh! Thank you.
-[Makani] Mm-hmm.

12:29.708 --> 12:31.708
-[girl 2] My fellow seniors.
-You think I'm bad?

12:32.291 --> 12:34.458
[girl 2] If may have
your attention, please.

12:34.958 --> 12:36.208
Thank you.

12:36.291 --> 12:39.333
I mean, what can one say
in the wake of such sadness?

12:39.833 --> 12:41.458
Yet as your student council president,

12:41.541 --> 12:44.041
I feel it's imperative
that I provide a beacon,

12:44.125 --> 12:48.041
a kind of guiding light
in these dark and trying times.

12:49.083 --> 12:53.000
So, I'd like to read an excerpt
from my admission essay to Cornell.

12:53.625 --> 12:54.583
It's about oppression.

12:55.166 --> 12:59.000
Princess Diana of Wales once said,
in her infinite wisdom,

12:59.083 --> 13:02.958
that, "The greatest problem
in the world today is intolerance."

13:03.541 --> 13:06.458
Did bitch just quote a princess
instead of someone actually oppressed?

13:06.541 --> 13:09.208
We have a student here at my school

13:09.291 --> 13:11.875
who is an outer space enthusiast,

13:11.958 --> 13:14.416
but that's not the only thing
about this student that's alien.

13:14.500 --> 13:17.250
His name, or her name,

13:17.333 --> 13:19.583
depending on the day, is Darby.

13:20.208 --> 13:24.416
Born Justine Darby, this student
showed me the meaning of courage

13:24.500 --> 13:28.041
when, at age 11, she came out
to our school as she, he, and they,

13:28.125 --> 13:30.083
and now every day in my mind,

13:30.166 --> 13:33.250
I applaud her, him, and them.

13:33.750 --> 13:35.875
[all applauding]

13:36.708 --> 13:38.125
[mouthing]

13:38.208 --> 13:42.291
[girl 2] Jackson's video
and his death were hateful,

13:42.375 --> 13:44.208
and the only way to respond to hate…

13:46.208 --> 13:47.041
is with love.

13:48.000 --> 13:50.583
We love all versions of you, Darby, okay?

13:50.666 --> 13:52.500
Like we love all versions of Caleb.

13:53.583 --> 13:54.958
So please, guys,

13:55.041 --> 13:58.500
let's celebrate that love tomorrow
at the memorial at Holy Trinity.

13:58.583 --> 14:01.500
For now, though, a moment of silent,

14:01.583 --> 14:04.500
unenforced, nondenominational prayer.

14:25.291 --> 14:27.291
Fuck these reactive people!

14:27.375 --> 14:29.500
All of our college essays are about you.
You know that?

14:29.583 --> 14:30.875
-I will cut you.
-[laughs]

14:31.666 --> 14:34.666
-It'd be great if Katie was the killer.
-Or if the killer maybe killed Katie.

14:34.750 --> 14:37.500
And you just said that. And I liked it.

14:37.583 --> 14:38.666
[students chuckling]

14:41.000 --> 14:44.166
-[Darby sighs]
-[Zach] "Sandford Family fucks."

14:46.500 --> 14:47.333
[sighs]

14:48.625 --> 14:49.458
I mean,

14:50.500 --> 14:51.583
it is factual.

14:52.291 --> 14:53.583
My dad is a fuck.

14:54.958 --> 14:56.416
-Wanna smoke?
-[Darby and Makani] Yes.

14:56.500 --> 14:59.833
-["Bite Me" by Kilo Kish playing]
-♪ I don't give a flying… Ahh! ♪

14:59.916 --> 15:01.583
♪ Bite me, bite me ♪

15:01.666 --> 15:03.708
♪ You can try me, try me ♪

15:03.791 --> 15:05.000
♪ If you likey… ♪

15:05.083 --> 15:06.458
Caleb seemed cool.

15:06.541 --> 15:08.333
[Alex and Zach laughing]

15:08.416 --> 15:10.958
Okay, okay, okay.
Let me rephrase that, you dicks.

15:12.208 --> 15:14.291
I like that you let him sit with us

15:14.375 --> 15:17.375
'cause that's what you guys did for me
when I first transferred here.

15:17.458 --> 15:19.333
Oh my God.
Those guys kept calling you Moana.

15:19.416 --> 15:20.333
I love that movie.

15:20.416 --> 15:23.458
-It's not really an insult.
-Not just those guys. That was Jackson.

15:23.541 --> 15:25.333
So you've been biding your time, huh?

15:25.416 --> 15:27.041
-[all laughing]
-[engine starts]

15:28.625 --> 15:29.791
-[tires screech]
-Oh shit!

15:29.875 --> 15:31.000
[Alex] Shit!

15:31.083 --> 15:33.125
Speaking of most likely to murder.

15:34.125 --> 15:35.416
[horn honking]

15:35.500 --> 15:36.916
Who even smokes cigarettes anymore?

15:37.000 --> 15:39.958
Oliver Larsson
because he's a fucking sociopath.

15:40.041 --> 15:41.750
You think everyone's a sociopath.

15:41.833 --> 15:44.541
[Alex] Yeah, but real talk,
his folks straight-up opted out of life

15:44.625 --> 15:46.291
'cause their son had zero human emotions.

15:47.208 --> 15:50.041
[sighs] I'm gonna opt out of life
if I don't hear about that fellowship.

15:50.791 --> 15:52.833
Last night, my mom said I could

15:52.916 --> 15:55.791
"always answer phones
at the slaughterhouse."

15:55.875 --> 15:59.083
Now I know why everyone
treats graduation like a death sentence.

15:59.166 --> 16:00.125
In Osborne, it is.

16:00.208 --> 16:02.666
[Darby] Except it's
literally the opposite of that.

16:02.750 --> 16:05.041
It is the opposite of the end.

16:05.125 --> 16:07.791
Yes. Yes!

16:07.875 --> 16:10.625
It's the opposite
of the end, motherfucker!

16:10.708 --> 16:13.250
-[all cheering]
-[horn honking]

16:13.333 --> 16:15.333
[crickets chirping]

16:21.125 --> 16:21.958
Just thought,

16:23.875 --> 16:25.250
"Here you are, Sabrina,

16:25.333 --> 16:28.208
asking your granddaughter
to take a big step with college and all,

16:28.291 --> 16:31.375
and I won't even take
a tiny step to fix my own stuff."

16:32.833 --> 16:35.125
So I signed up for next month.

16:35.208 --> 16:36.875
Or if you just drank your tea.

16:36.958 --> 16:38.166
Oh, man.

16:40.083 --> 16:42.041
Heard you walking around last night.

16:42.125 --> 16:44.625
You don't think I notice
you changing the subject?

16:45.541 --> 16:49.500
Honey, I'm sure all this horrible stuff
at school is dredging up memories.

16:49.583 --> 16:52.083
You need to focus here
on your application.

16:52.166 --> 16:55.041
What's the point?
All they have to do is Google my name,

16:55.125 --> 16:56.375
my real name,

16:57.541 --> 17:00.958
and then all that financial aid
and friends I might've made is just,

17:01.625 --> 17:03.583
"Bye." So what's the point?

17:03.666 --> 17:06.708
The point is that's not you anymore.

17:07.333 --> 17:09.333
I see you up there
in your mama's old room,

17:09.416 --> 17:12.041
all her old stuff still on the walls.

17:12.125 --> 17:14.000
Like you don't even have a say.

17:14.666 --> 17:17.875
You have to stop blaming yourself
for what happened.

17:23.416 --> 17:24.375
[Makani] Okay.

17:26.750 --> 17:28.750
But you gotta drink that tea for me.

17:29.333 --> 17:30.208
Oh.

17:30.291 --> 17:32.416
["Wasteland" by Tierra Whack playing]

17:34.958 --> 17:35.791
[bell jingles]

17:35.875 --> 17:38.083
♪ I got bigger fish to fry ♪

17:38.166 --> 17:39.916
♪ I can't tell a lie ♪

17:40.000 --> 17:41.833
♪ Walk away from me ♪

17:41.916 --> 17:43.666
♪ That's my best advice ♪

17:43.750 --> 17:45.500
♪ Chillin' in the hills ♪

17:45.583 --> 17:47.416
♪ Hills have eyes ♪

17:47.500 --> 17:49.291
♪ Can't be seen with you ♪

17:49.375 --> 17:51.125
♪ You don't match my fly ♪

17:51.208 --> 17:53.000
♪ Try to buy me lunch ♪

17:53.083 --> 17:54.500
♪ You gon' pay the price ♪

17:54.583 --> 17:56.750
♪ Baby, play your role ♪

17:56.833 --> 17:59.000
-♪ Don't forget your lines ♪
-[phone chimes]

17:59.083 --> 18:00.541
♪ It's a long line, it's a wait ♪

18:00.625 --> 18:02.708
♪ Asked me, could he take me on a date… ♪

18:07.541 --> 18:08.791
[bell jingling]

18:11.333 --> 18:13.666
-Good night, Gam.
-[Gam] Good night, hon.

