39:04.958 --> 39:07.250
[girl 1] I eat junk food all the time
and never gain weight,

39:07.333 --> 39:09.000
and people hate me for it.

39:09.083 --> 39:12.000
So, your secret's you're perfect?
Fuck off.

39:12.916 --> 39:16.208
I have a YouTube channel
where I try to sing opera.

39:16.291 --> 39:17.708
Oh my God, I know.

39:17.791 --> 39:19.833
-Wait. You're the one who's watching?
-Yes.

39:20.500 --> 39:23.250
[girl 2] Last year I had a miscarriage.

39:23.333 --> 39:26.583
Wait, are we telling real secrets?

39:26.666 --> 39:28.750
[overlapping chattering]

39:28.833 --> 39:30.291
Secret party.

39:30.375 --> 39:32.166
[screams, laughs]

39:32.250 --> 39:33.666
It's about time!

39:33.750 --> 39:35.500
Oh my God! Come on!

39:35.583 --> 39:37.791
[boy 3] I find myself
attracted to my cousin.

39:37.875 --> 39:40.625
[Alex] Rodrigo, move!
This is your drink. Drink this.

39:45.666 --> 39:46.500
[mouthing]

39:46.583 --> 39:48.583
[Alex] You know,
I accidentally ran over a hitchhiker

39:48.666 --> 39:51.416
and dumped his body into the ocean.
Is that bad? 'Cause I can't tell.

39:51.500 --> 39:55.125
Wait, sorry, but everyone's
just telling each other their secrets?

39:55.208 --> 39:56.291
[Zach] Genius, right?

39:56.375 --> 40:00.000
By publicly admitting the one thing
the killer's using against us,

40:00.083 --> 40:01.416
we're taking away his only weapon.

40:01.500 --> 40:03.291
Except for, like, when it's a knife.

40:03.375 --> 40:05.750
There's no way your dad
sanctioned this, though.

40:05.833 --> 40:08.416
Sadly, Skipper's en route
to a big-game safari

40:08.500 --> 40:10.333
he couldn't possibly pass up, so…

40:10.416 --> 40:11.666
Can we help you?

40:12.625 --> 40:13.583
Yeah, you.

40:13.666 --> 40:17.250
All-in-black, school-shooter-style icon,
you keep looking at us.

40:18.000 --> 40:19.083
Do you have a secret?

40:19.166 --> 40:23.166
Would you like to unburden yourself,
or are you just creeping like a creep?

40:23.250 --> 40:25.541
Hey, man!
Everyone knows you're a sociopath!

40:25.625 --> 40:27.333
[scoffs] Ro!

40:28.000 --> 40:30.000
Oh my God, guys. That was really mean.

40:30.083 --> 40:31.208
No! No, it wasn't.

40:31.291 --> 40:33.458
-[chuckles]
-I might have a real confession.

40:37.833 --> 40:39.041
-I got in.
-[Alex gasps]

40:39.125 --> 40:41.083
-What?
-Oh my-- You got in!

40:41.166 --> 40:43.833
-Oh my God!
-Oh my God! No way!

40:43.916 --> 40:45.000
[Alex squealing]

40:45.083 --> 40:47.125
-Don't make me cry. Don't make me cry.
-Okay.

40:47.208 --> 40:49.333
Okay, all right. Okay, okay, okay. Okay.

40:50.583 --> 40:52.291
I have a secret. [clears throat]

40:52.375 --> 40:54.916
Really? I thought
we were the ones with no secrets.

40:55.000 --> 40:58.958
I have a secret crush on…

40:59.041 --> 41:00.375
[clicking tongue]

41:02.458 --> 41:04.541
Because you're dead-ass funny

41:04.625 --> 41:06.416
in such a low-frequency way,

41:06.500 --> 41:09.125
but I hear it, and I love it.

41:09.208 --> 41:12.291
All right, all right! This is fun!
All right! Rodrigo, go.

41:12.375 --> 41:13.458
What's your secret?

41:15.500 --> 41:17.625
-Same.
-[yelps, laughs]

41:17.708 --> 41:19.708
-[Caleb] What?
-Wait, really?

41:22.833 --> 41:23.708
Um, Makani?

41:26.333 --> 41:27.250
Um,

41:28.916 --> 41:30.125
I write poetry.

41:30.208 --> 41:31.583
[Alex] Wait, really? No way.

41:32.166 --> 41:35.208
And, uh, I'm not gonna graduate.

41:35.708 --> 41:37.041
How's this for poetry?

41:37.958 --> 41:41.875
"This letter's to inform you
that your son, Zachariah Sandford,

41:41.958 --> 41:43.833
is at risk of failing classes."

41:43.916 --> 41:47.541
"His current GPA is a one-point fucked."

41:48.041 --> 41:51.541
[sucks teeth] Yeah,
but that's not the real secret.

41:51.625 --> 41:53.250
The real secret--

41:53.333 --> 41:54.916
-[partygoers exclaiming]
-Shit.

41:55.000 --> 41:57.875
Whoa, whoa! Guys, whoa! Chill, chill.

41:58.458 --> 42:01.625
The only thing
it's loaded with is meaning.

42:03.166 --> 42:04.750
-[girl 1] What? No!
-[girl 2] Oh, my God!

42:04.833 --> 42:06.291
-Zach! Zach!
-Dude!

42:06.375 --> 42:07.458
[Alex] What the hell?

42:10.666 --> 42:12.333
-[people sighing]
-[boy] Dude!

42:12.416 --> 42:17.041
-Crazy.
-Which brings me to tonight's main event.

42:17.791 --> 42:18.625
[boy 1] Ooh.

42:20.041 --> 42:21.833
[partygoers chattering]

42:21.916 --> 42:23.791
-[Zach] You laugh at me.
-[partygoers] Yeah.

42:23.875 --> 42:25.875
-You make fun of me.
-[partygoers] Yeah.

42:25.958 --> 42:28.458
You… you… you tag my truck.

42:28.541 --> 42:30.875
-Fuck yeah, we did!
-[partygoers laughing]

42:30.958 --> 42:33.375
[Zach] I get it. It makes sense.

42:34.166 --> 42:38.166
You think that my father
is this festering pustule

42:38.250 --> 42:41.208
disguised as a God-fearing pillar
of the community.

42:41.791 --> 42:45.458
He buys up your families' land
for pennies on the dollar.

42:45.541 --> 42:46.958
And for what?

42:47.041 --> 42:51.583
Just so he can grow his 30,000-plus
acre corporate empire of shit!

42:51.666 --> 42:53.041
-Fuck that shit!
-[girl] Yeah.

42:53.125 --> 42:55.833
But, what if I told you…

42:57.833 --> 43:02.291
Skipper Sandford's collection
extended far beyond corn…

43:03.666 --> 43:05.500
-[partygoers] Whoa!
-[boy 2] What?

43:05.583 --> 43:10.041
…and included the tenth largest
Nazi memorabilia collection

43:10.125 --> 43:11.333
in all of North America?

43:11.416 --> 43:13.083
[boy 3] That's fucked up.

43:13.708 --> 43:15.375
A shocking amount of which

43:15.458 --> 43:16.958
I have converted

43:17.041 --> 43:21.250
into pipes, hookahs, and bongs.

43:21.333 --> 43:23.791
-[partygoers laughing]
-[boy 4] Of course!

43:23.875 --> 43:25.291
[boy 5] Dude, no way!

43:25.375 --> 43:28.791
-That's crazy.
-So, allow me to propose a toast.

43:29.916 --> 43:32.958
The 1% is burning down
the world so they can stay warm.

43:33.541 --> 43:36.333
I say, "Let it burn down them too."

43:36.416 --> 43:37.541
[boy 6] Yeah!

43:37.625 --> 43:39.625
While we burn down Highway 420.

43:40.250 --> 43:42.291
[partygoers] Whoo!

43:43.791 --> 43:45.083
[cheering]

43:46.833 --> 43:48.333
["Go Up" by Gizzle playing]

43:49.583 --> 43:51.500
♪ Gimme some, some of that ♪

43:51.583 --> 43:53.583
♪ Some of this, some of that ♪

43:53.666 --> 43:55.458
♪ How you gonna do me like that? ♪

43:55.541 --> 43:57.541
♪ Walk in here looking
Like a movie like that ♪

43:57.625 --> 43:59.750
♪ You know I'm coming back
If you move it like that ♪

43:59.833 --> 44:01.291
♪ One, make you melt like the sun ♪

44:01.375 --> 44:03.291
♪ Two, I could make it all about you ♪

44:03.375 --> 44:05.166
♪ Three, you should make it all about me ♪

44:05.250 --> 44:07.583
♪ Four, yeah, I think I like that more ♪

44:07.666 --> 44:09.916
♪ Sheesh, just real clean
Like James Dean ♪

44:10.000 --> 44:12.000
♪ I could make you go mainstream ♪

44:12.083 --> 44:14.083
♪ I could help you reach your dreams
Bada boom ♪

44:14.166 --> 44:15.500
♪ Bada bing, yeah ♪

44:15.583 --> 44:17.375
♪ When we go around, we go up ♪

44:17.958 --> 44:19.916
♪ Never come down, we go up ♪

44:20.000 --> 44:23.458
♪ When we come around, they know us
Go up, go up, go up, go up ♪

44:29.791 --> 44:31.625
♪ Gimme some, some of that ♪

44:31.708 --> 44:33.708
♪ Some of this, some of that ♪

44:33.791 --> 44:35.208
♪ Gimme some, some of that ♪

44:35.291 --> 44:37.708
[dance music playing in background]

44:39.500 --> 44:41.666
[both moaning]

44:41.750 --> 44:43.458
[Alex] Wait, wait, wait. You, uh…

44:44.291 --> 44:46.625
You meant it, right?
You weren't just saying that?

44:46.708 --> 44:47.958
I'm your secret?

44:50.375 --> 44:51.416
-[banging on door]
-[gasps]

44:53.083 --> 44:54.500
What… what do you want?

44:55.541 --> 44:57.041
-[Macon] Chips?
-[sighs]

45:01.041 --> 45:03.083
-[Macon] Salt and vinegar?
-Fuck off!

45:03.166 --> 45:05.166
-[whispers] Sorry.
-[Rodrigo chuckles]

45:05.750 --> 45:07.625
You're my secret. Yeah.

45:09.541 --> 45:10.958
I see you, Ro.

45:12.208 --> 45:13.500
I always have.

45:14.333 --> 45:15.250
[chuckles]

45:25.500 --> 45:28.250
[dance music playing in background]

45:28.333 --> 45:29.333
So,

45:30.291 --> 45:31.666
see you back with the others?

45:32.250 --> 45:34.250
Yeah. Thank you.

45:34.833 --> 45:36.708
Did… did you just thank me?

45:37.958 --> 45:39.000
-No.
-[Alex laughs]

45:39.083 --> 45:42.125
Sorry, that… that would be…
that would be… would be stupid.

45:52.416 --> 45:54.000
[ominous music playing]

46:01.583 --> 46:04.000
[breathing heavily]

46:23.041 --> 46:25.333
[phones chiming]

46:31.500 --> 46:32.875
Did you make this?

46:33.625 --> 46:36.750
-Your secret's you're taking painkillers?
-[boy 1] Fentanyl?

46:37.250 --> 46:39.291
Oh, that shit's for junkies.

46:40.375 --> 46:43.333
-[boy 2] Yo, what's going on?
-[Zach] Who the fuck turned out my lights?

46:43.416 --> 46:45.791
-[boy 3] Power go out?
-[Rodrigo panting] Alex!

46:45.875 --> 46:47.041
[Alex] Rodrigo!

46:47.125 --> 46:49.083
-Rodrigo, we're over here!
-[phone chimes]

46:49.166 --> 46:50.666
[Rodrigo] Guys, where are you?

46:51.291 --> 46:52.541
Zach, what's going on, man?

46:54.708 --> 46:57.833
Shit! There's someone
wearing Rodrigo's fucking face!

46:57.916 --> 47:00.333
-[girl] The killer's here!
-[partygoers screaming]

47:00.416 --> 47:01.875
Alex! Alex!

47:01.958 --> 47:04.625
It just numbs me out
so I don't think so much!

47:04.708 --> 47:06.208
I'm always in my head!

47:06.291 --> 47:07.375
[Alex] Rodrigo!

47:07.458 --> 47:08.541
[Rodrigo] Alex!

47:08.625 --> 47:09.791
[partygoers clamoring]

47:11.916 --> 47:13.500
-[Darby] Rodrigo!
-I see him!

47:15.041 --> 47:17.541
I see him! Help, please!

47:17.625 --> 47:18.500
Help!

47:20.833 --> 47:21.875
[grunts]

47:23.208 --> 47:24.333
[panting]

47:41.833 --> 47:43.041
[footsteps approaching]

47:48.041 --> 47:49.625
[breathing shakily]

47:51.541 --> 47:52.625
Oh God.

47:58.500 --> 47:59.708
[footsteps departing]

48:00.541 --> 48:02.125
[breathing deeply]

48:03.166 --> 48:04.916
-[phone vibrates, chimes]
-Shit.

48:05.500 --> 48:06.958
[grunting]

48:07.041 --> 48:08.125
[panting]

48:13.208 --> 48:14.958
[grunting]

48:18.375 --> 48:19.916
[panting]

48:28.041 --> 48:29.041
[gasping]

48:31.833 --> 48:32.791
Oh!

48:33.375 --> 48:34.458
[panting]

48:41.583 --> 48:42.583
[grunting]

48:44.416 --> 48:46.083
[girl] Come on, come on, we gotta go!

48:48.291 --> 48:49.416
[grunts]

48:49.500 --> 48:51.166
[panting]

48:51.750 --> 48:52.708
[screams, grunts]

48:52.791 --> 48:54.291
[Taser clicking]

48:55.416 --> 48:56.791
[grunting]

48:57.375 --> 49:00.750
[sinister music playing]

49:00.833 --> 49:02.166
[continues grunting]

49:07.291 --> 49:09.083
[gagging]

49:09.166 --> 49:12.583
[coughing]

49:13.333 --> 49:15.083
[blade ringing]

49:15.166 --> 49:17.041
[gagging]

49:38.250 --> 49:40.541
[ethereal music playing]

50:56.666 --> 50:58.958
[girls laughing]

51:03.958 --> 51:05.750
[girls screaming]

51:10.791 --> 51:12.166
[birds chirping]

51:17.583 --> 51:20.666
[announcer] The Wampus Cats have
their first game in three weeks tonight.

51:20.750 --> 51:23.000
So let's go out
and celebrate the dearly departed

51:23.083 --> 51:26.166
with a little Osborne pride.
Officers will be on hand

51:26.250 --> 51:29.083
to ensure the safety and security
of everyone in attendance.

51:29.166 --> 51:32.666
[players] Whoo! [cheering]

51:32.750 --> 51:35.708
Everyone's just moved on, I guess.

51:35.791 --> 51:37.833
You're all coming to the game, right?

51:39.083 --> 51:40.458
Sorry about your friend.

51:43.708 --> 51:46.666
Just something I did to honor him.

51:50.625 --> 51:52.708
You don't have anything to say about this?

51:52.791 --> 51:55.416
I'm done talking about who I think did it.

51:56.708 --> 51:57.625
I know who did it.

52:03.666 --> 52:05.791
And now everyone else does too.

52:09.083 --> 52:10.291
[grunting]

52:10.375 --> 52:11.916
-[whistle blows]
-[crowd] Ohh!

52:12.000 --> 52:15.208
-Why are you even defending him right now?
-I'm not. I just…

52:15.791 --> 52:20.041
I mean, imagine if it were you, or D,
or Zach people were whispering about.

52:20.125 --> 52:24.333
[cheerleaders] Full comeback!
Who's that? The Wampus Cat!

52:24.916 --> 52:26.541
Makani, you were at the party!

52:26.625 --> 52:28.416
I called him out. He heard me!

52:28.500 --> 52:32.125
Then Rodrigo talked shit,
and within one hour, Rodrigo is just…

52:32.208 --> 52:35.125
I hear you, okay?
I don't know what you want me to say.

52:35.208 --> 52:38.416
-Call the cops if you're so sure.
-They said she has no evidence.

52:38.500 --> 52:41.375
-'Cause she doesn't.
-Because his brother's the deputy!

52:41.458 --> 52:43.000
[players grunting]

52:43.083 --> 52:45.000
The killer used a Taser, babe.

52:45.083 --> 52:46.791
Who uses Tasers? Cops!

52:46.875 --> 52:48.250
And who lives with a cop?

52:48.333 --> 52:52.458
Giving him access to background checks
about everyone in town, including us.

52:53.166 --> 52:54.125
[grunting]

52:54.208 --> 52:56.000
[crowd cheering]

52:56.083 --> 52:58.083
Katie's podcast was anonymous.

52:58.583 --> 53:02.083
Guess who can request
connection logs from ISPs? Piggy pigs.

53:02.625 --> 53:04.708
-[grunting]
-Makani, you weren't here growing up.

53:05.750 --> 53:08.000
He was a disturbed kid in a real way.

53:09.625 --> 53:11.416
Do you even know
what happened to his parents?

53:12.750 --> 53:13.833
[cheering]

53:15.083 --> 53:16.958
[Caleb] Whoo! Whoo!

53:18.208 --> 53:19.166
Go, Caleb!

53:19.250 --> 53:20.083
Whoo!

53:22.208 --> 53:24.416
[Alex] Look at all the team all happy,

53:24.500 --> 53:26.666
so into gays
when they can win football games.

53:26.750 --> 53:28.708
Do you just fucking hate everyone?

53:28.791 --> 53:31.625
[somber music playing]

53:36.333 --> 53:37.166
[phone chimes]

53:47.500 --> 53:49.416
Tell me you didn't forget.

53:49.500 --> 53:54.000
-Right. Sleep clinic thing.
-[Gam] Baby, I don't want you here alone.

53:54.083 --> 53:56.583
You told me you were gonna stay
at Alexandra's tomorrow night.

53:56.666 --> 54:00.041
Yeah, yeah. I, um,
was literally just texting her about it.

54:00.958 --> 54:01.916
Proud of you.

54:03.166 --> 54:06.458
The things I do
to get that infernal bell off my door.

54:17.041 --> 54:18.125
[doorbell rings]

54:23.958 --> 54:24.791
[Makani] Oh.

54:25.291 --> 54:26.916
You just showed up.

54:29.166 --> 54:31.708
I thought I'd take you
on a trip to the ocean.

54:32.375 --> 54:34.750
Pretty sure that's, like,
a thousand miles away.

54:35.250 --> 54:36.750
Not the one I'm thinking of.

54:37.333 --> 54:40.500
["All Mirrors" (Johnny Jewel Remix)
by Angel Olsen playing]

54:40.583 --> 54:44.333
♪ I've been watchin' ♪

54:44.416 --> 54:48.750
♪ All of my past repeatin' ♪

54:49.625 --> 54:53.833
♪ There's no endin' ♪

54:53.916 --> 54:57.458
♪ And when I stop pretendin'… ♪

54:58.041 --> 54:59.125
[laughs]

54:59.625 --> 55:01.583
Who even smokes cigarettes anymore?

55:02.166 --> 55:05.041
Just nice pretending
to have control over how we die.

55:22.208 --> 55:23.291
[engine turns off]

55:24.458 --> 55:25.375
[Makani groans]

55:27.875 --> 55:29.833
I thought you were taking me to the beach.

55:29.916 --> 55:31.875
Nope, the ocean.

55:34.166 --> 55:35.958
Don't worry. The car's a piece of shit.

55:39.833 --> 55:40.875
-Okay?
-Mm-hmm.

55:43.541 --> 55:44.375
[exhales deeply]

55:44.875 --> 55:46.125
[cornstalks rustling]

55:50.791 --> 55:52.625
It's not exactly the Pacific but…

55:54.583 --> 55:55.625
the fields.

56:09.875 --> 56:11.333
"Let it be forgotten

56:13.708 --> 56:15.416
As a flower is forgotten,

56:17.291 --> 56:20.041
Forgotten as a fire
That once was singing gold,

56:22.083 --> 56:24.500
Let it be forgotten forever and ever,

56:26.625 --> 56:28.375
Time is a kind friend,

56:29.416 --> 56:30.916
She will make us old."

56:37.666 --> 56:38.791
When'd you write that?

56:42.291 --> 56:43.125
[grunts]

56:53.291 --> 56:54.791
Don't shut me out again.

56:56.208 --> 56:57.291
Stay here.

56:58.833 --> 56:59.916
Like this.

57:01.333 --> 57:05.000
-Good thing I know you're not dangerous.
-I mean, I never said that.

57:08.500 --> 57:11.500
Maybe that's why I brought you
out here in the first place, you know?

57:13.416 --> 57:15.166
Where no one can find us.

57:17.208 --> 57:19.625
Well, you'd have to know my secret first.

57:19.708 --> 57:20.833
You think I don't?

57:55.083 --> 57:57.708
[whispering] I actually
think you love secrets.

57:59.375 --> 58:02.000
You still won't tell
a single soul about me.

58:06.291 --> 58:07.416
[phone vibrating]

58:12.250 --> 58:13.791
Fucking Chris.

58:15.625 --> 58:18.375
He'll just keep calling
and keep calling, so I'm, uh…

58:18.458 --> 58:20.375
-Yeah.
-Yeah. Sorry.

58:25.125 --> 58:27.250
Hi. What do you want?

58:30.833 --> 58:31.875
Not far.

58:33.041 --> 58:33.916
Yes.

58:36.083 --> 58:37.291
I don't know. Soon.

58:37.375 --> 58:38.708
[ominous music playing]

58:40.208 --> 58:41.625
[Makani breathing shakily]

58:42.416 --> 58:43.458
Okay.

58:44.000 --> 58:45.083
Bye.

58:45.166 --> 58:46.708
[Makani panting]

58:49.416 --> 58:51.583
He always has to know
where I am all the time.

58:53.500 --> 58:54.791
-[sighs]
-Did you tell him?

58:54.875 --> 58:55.791
No.

58:56.916 --> 58:59.000
Still thinks he can be my dad, you know?

59:05.041 --> 59:06.708
You never talk about them,

59:08.208 --> 59:09.208
your parents.

59:10.916 --> 59:12.000
What happened?

59:17.166 --> 59:18.208
Sorry.

59:18.958 --> 59:21.625
We can… we can just go. [clears throat]

59:23.583 --> 59:25.250
They crashed into a tree.

59:29.333 --> 59:30.916
My dad was driving.

59:32.000 --> 59:33.916
It killed him instantly, and, um,

59:35.750 --> 59:40.250
my mom, she, um…
she died in the hospital the next day.

59:42.166 --> 59:44.333
I mean, they were drunks, you know?

59:44.416 --> 59:49.666
Always were, but that part gets,
like, left out conveniently.

59:50.500 --> 59:53.833
But it makes for a better legend,
I guess, when it's some

59:54.666 --> 59:59.166
dramatic double suicide
'cause a kid had behavioral issues.

1:00:02.583 --> 1:00:05.500
You know, I just think, like,
when something really terrible happens,

1:00:05.583 --> 1:00:08.583
people need someone to blame.

1:00:09.958 --> 1:00:12.166
No one probably gets that better than you.

1:00:14.375 --> 1:00:17.000
I mean, that's what those poems are about,

1:00:18.166 --> 1:00:19.041
right?

1:00:19.750 --> 1:00:20.625
What?

1:00:21.375 --> 1:00:22.500
Being blamed.

1:00:25.541 --> 1:00:27.583
Did you do a background check on me?

1:00:31.333 --> 1:00:32.166
Makani.

1:00:33.916 --> 1:00:36.000
Makani, wait! Stop!

1:00:37.958 --> 1:00:39.041
Makani!

1:00:40.541 --> 1:00:42.000
Makani Sun-woo.

1:00:43.375 --> 1:00:44.416
I know you.

1:00:45.833 --> 1:00:47.375
I know who you are.

1:00:50.250 --> 1:00:52.250
What are you gonna do? Hitchhike?

1:00:52.333 --> 1:00:53.958
[ominous music playing]

1:00:54.041 --> 1:00:57.208
["Adriatic Flow" by ThreeStyle
featuring Magdalena Chovancova playing]

1:00:57.291 --> 1:00:58.625
[Dave] World got you down?

1:00:59.750 --> 1:01:00.625
We can talk.

1:01:01.833 --> 1:01:02.833
I won't judge.

1:01:03.750 --> 1:01:07.625
I am but an observer of human behavior.

1:01:07.708 --> 1:01:08.708
[chuckles]

1:01:09.416 --> 1:01:12.666
You get people alone in a car,
you can learn real quick who they are,

1:01:13.708 --> 1:01:16.541
especially when they feel
like you work for 'em.

1:01:17.041 --> 1:01:19.541
[inhales] Like that churchy girl
who got strung up.

1:01:19.625 --> 1:01:22.916
Could've told you she was talking
out of both sides of her mouth.

1:01:23.416 --> 1:01:25.583
She was a real bitch, that one.

1:01:26.291 --> 1:01:27.416
May she rest.

1:01:27.916 --> 1:01:28.958
Mmm.

1:01:29.958 --> 1:01:32.208
Wasn't too good at hiding it either.

1:01:33.500 --> 1:01:34.541
Not like you.

1:01:35.166 --> 1:01:36.000
Hmm?

1:01:37.333 --> 1:01:39.166
You're a nice girl, aren't you?

1:01:41.541 --> 1:01:42.375
Yeah.

1:01:42.958 --> 1:01:46.000
It's always nice
to have a nice girl in the car.

1:01:53.833 --> 1:01:55.500
Are you here all alone?

1:01:56.708 --> 1:01:58.750
No. My parents
just go to bed really early.

1:01:59.375 --> 1:02:01.791
-Ah…
-Five stars. Thanks, Dave. See ya.

1:02:01.875 --> 1:02:02.875
Yeah.

1:02:03.791 --> 1:02:04.833
See you.

1:02:19.125 --> 1:02:21.291
[ominous music playing]

1:02:32.208 --> 1:02:33.125
[sighs]

1:02:45.291 --> 1:02:47.500
[fire crackling]

1:02:48.708 --> 1:02:51.041
[bell jingling]

1:02:58.791 --> 1:03:00.208
[breathing heavily]

1:03:06.125 --> 1:03:07.708
[exhales sharply] Gam?

1:03:09.708 --> 1:03:11.916
-[bell jingling]
-[breathing shakily]

1:03:14.833 --> 1:03:15.791
[gasps]

1:03:20.916 --> 1:03:21.916
[dialing phone]

1:03:23.208 --> 1:03:25.583
[line ringing]

1:03:26.416 --> 1:03:27.875
[Makani's voice over phone]
Not a day goes by

1:03:27.958 --> 1:03:29.875
I don't hate myself for it, Your Honor.

1:03:30.625 --> 1:03:32.166
If I could switch places

1:03:32.250 --> 1:03:34.958
and be the one
who went into that fire, I would.

1:03:35.041 --> 1:03:36.375
-[phone beeps]
-[gasping]

1:03:36.458 --> 1:03:37.583
[shudders]

1:03:37.666 --> 1:03:40.833
[fire crackling]

1:03:40.916 --> 1:03:42.916
[Makani breathing heavily]

1:03:45.416 --> 1:03:47.583
[sinister music playing]

1:03:53.166 --> 1:03:54.125
Ollie?

1:04:11.833 --> 1:04:14.000
[crying]

1:04:52.375 --> 1:04:53.500
[sobbing]

1:04:56.958 --> 1:04:58.208
[gasping]

1:04:59.833 --> 1:05:02.666
-[Taser clicking]
-[whimpering]

1:05:09.791 --> 1:05:11.750
[whimpering]

1:05:15.625 --> 1:05:16.541
No!

1:05:16.625 --> 1:05:17.750
[sobbing]

1:05:19.041 --> 1:05:20.375
[coughing]

1:05:25.916 --> 1:05:27.875
[sobbing] No. No!

1:05:28.458 --> 1:05:30.625
[sobbing continues]

1:05:45.416 --> 1:05:46.791
[car approaching]

1:05:48.125 --> 1:05:49.291
[grunts]

1:05:51.083 --> 1:05:52.125
[Alex] Makani?

1:05:52.208 --> 1:05:53.208
[grunting]

1:05:54.208 --> 1:05:55.958
[sobbing]

1:05:56.041 --> 1:05:57.833
-[knocking on door]
-[Alex] Makani?

1:05:57.916 --> 1:05:59.416
[door rattling]

1:05:59.500 --> 1:06:01.708
I'm at her house right now. Makani?

1:06:02.291 --> 1:06:04.875
Your grandma called. Are you-- Jesus!

1:06:04.958 --> 1:06:07.791
Yeah, my friend's been attacked.
1412 Prescott! Hurry!

1:06:07.875 --> 1:06:11.000
-[woman] Sending a patrol car right away.
-[sobbing] It was Ollie. It was Ollie!

1:06:11.666 --> 1:06:12.750
You were right.

1:06:12.833 --> 1:06:15.291
[sobbing] They're gonna know.

1:06:15.375 --> 1:06:16.916
They're all gonna know.

1:06:17.000 --> 1:06:17.958
Know what?

1:06:18.041 --> 1:06:20.000
[sobbing continues]

1:06:20.083 --> 1:06:20.916
[phone chimes]

1:06:24.625 --> 1:06:27.041
[sinister music playing]

1:06:40.958 --> 1:06:41.791
Mmm.

1:06:45.500 --> 1:06:46.958
Hey, baby.

1:06:49.333 --> 1:06:50.333
What?

1:06:51.625 --> 1:06:53.125
He was there.

1:06:55.416 --> 1:06:57.375
Gam, he was there. He was there.

1:06:57.458 --> 1:06:58.708
They got him, sweetie.

1:06:58.791 --> 1:07:00.500
-They found him.
-You're safe.

1:07:01.083 --> 1:07:02.083
[Gam] It's okay.

1:07:02.666 --> 1:07:03.541
You're okay.

1:07:04.041 --> 1:07:05.333
We're all here.

1:07:08.666 --> 1:07:10.041
Did he text everyone?

1:07:11.333 --> 1:07:13.125
[Darby] I stopped reading.

1:07:13.208 --> 1:07:17.458
Thought you'd maybe like us
to hear it, you know, from you.

1:07:20.750 --> 1:07:23.375
I'm gonna get a coffee.

1:07:23.458 --> 1:07:24.666
Give you a few.

1:07:37.041 --> 1:07:38.458
[girl] Open your eyes.

1:07:39.791 --> 1:07:41.500
[girls laughing]

1:07:42.375 --> 1:07:47.208
Okay, bitches. You think
you got what it takes to win State?

1:07:47.958 --> 1:07:49.750
'Cause I don't see shit.

1:07:49.833 --> 1:07:51.791
[girls continue laughing]

1:07:51.875 --> 1:07:53.500
What's your name, bitch?

1:07:57.583 --> 1:07:59.583
[gagging]

1:07:59.666 --> 1:08:02.416
-Hold up. These girls kidnapped you?
-These were your friends?

1:08:03.166 --> 1:08:05.541
Sometimes friends, I don't know.

1:08:06.458 --> 1:08:09.541
They were seniors.
It was my first year on varsity.

1:08:10.125 --> 1:08:12.083
-Varsity what?
-You played sports?

1:08:12.166 --> 1:08:14.500
[girl] Are you a hungry little bitch?

1:08:14.583 --> 1:08:15.833
[girls laughing]

1:08:15.916 --> 1:08:17.000
Cow!

1:08:17.083 --> 1:08:18.750
[gasping, gagging]

1:08:19.416 --> 1:08:21.000
[girl] Drink up, bitches!

1:08:21.083 --> 1:08:24.916
[Makani] They were hazing us.
Tried to get us to turn on each other.

1:08:25.000 --> 1:08:28.416
-[girl] You can do better than that!
-[Makani] We were out of our minds.

1:08:28.500 --> 1:08:30.458
[girl] How's that taste, Makani, huh?

1:08:32.208 --> 1:08:33.583
Hey, Jasmine.

1:08:37.958 --> 1:08:39.666
[gasps, screams]

1:08:45.708 --> 1:08:46.666
I just…

1:08:48.666 --> 1:08:49.625
pushed.

1:08:51.166 --> 1:08:55.583
Jasmine survived, but there were burns.

1:08:57.333 --> 1:08:59.000
Her face was, um…

1:09:02.958 --> 1:09:06.083
I got charged and went to trial.

1:09:08.208 --> 1:09:11.083
Even after I was acquitted,
I still got threats

1:09:12.083 --> 1:09:12.958
daily.

1:09:15.416 --> 1:09:17.208
My parents blamed each other.

1:09:18.083 --> 1:09:21.250
[scoffs] They'd been looking
for a reason to break up anyway.

1:09:25.708 --> 1:09:30.166
I was so ashamed of myself.

1:09:32.375 --> 1:09:33.833
So I moved here.

1:09:36.125 --> 1:09:39.500
Took my mom's maiden name and just…

1:09:40.541 --> 1:09:43.375
[sighs] …tried to become
a different person.

1:09:43.458 --> 1:09:44.833
You are a different person.

1:09:45.500 --> 1:09:47.833
I've never met
the person you're talking about.

1:09:48.458 --> 1:09:52.083
You bring me doughnuts
because you know they soothe me.

1:09:52.708 --> 1:09:56.916
You proofread my essays.
You stand up for me in public.

1:09:57.000 --> 1:09:58.583
That's who you are.

1:09:59.791 --> 1:10:03.125
I mean, you gave Ollie Larsson
the benefit of the doubt.

1:10:03.208 --> 1:10:04.541
And he's a murderer.

1:10:04.625 --> 1:10:07.750
Yeah, you gave a fucking murderer
the chance to show he's decent.

1:10:11.916 --> 1:10:14.416
-To no more secrets between friends.
-[chuckles]

1:10:14.500 --> 1:10:16.708
It's a fucking hospital, Zach!
Wait till we get her home!

1:10:16.791 --> 1:10:20.583
I'm not saying that we have to smoke it.
It… it's symbolic.

1:10:21.708 --> 1:10:23.458
I'm not really good with hugs.

1:10:26.250 --> 1:10:28.125
-[Alex] Come on.
-[Makani chuckles]

1:10:37.750 --> 1:10:40.916
[reporter] KRDY News has learned
that the Sloan County sheriffs

1:10:41.000 --> 1:10:42.125
have made an arrest,

1:10:42.208 --> 1:10:44.958
and suspect Oliver Larsson is in custody.

1:10:45.041 --> 1:10:47.875
A sense of calm has returned
to this small Nebraska town,

1:10:47.958 --> 1:10:51.666
and plans to move forward
with the Corn in the USA Festival next--

1:10:55.708 --> 1:10:56.708
[sighs]

1:11:30.791 --> 1:11:31.875
[country music playing]

1:11:31.958 --> 1:11:35.625
[Skipper] This year, the Fall Harvest
Festival should be a celebration.

1:11:35.708 --> 1:11:38.750
People here, they have
a right to feel safe, protected,

1:11:38.833 --> 1:11:44.000
and our little police force, good men all,
but they are sadly undermanned.

1:11:44.083 --> 1:11:47.000
That's why
Sandford Family Farms has stepped in.

1:11:47.083 --> 1:11:48.958
We've hired private security,

1:11:49.041 --> 1:11:50.625
free of charge.

1:11:50.708 --> 1:11:52.125
Our little gift.

1:11:52.208 --> 1:11:53.333
These men are here

1:11:53.416 --> 1:11:56.750
so people can enjoy themselves
and these fine festivities.

1:11:57.583 --> 1:12:02.333
Nothing, absolutely nothing's
gonna stop this proud corn town

1:12:02.416 --> 1:12:04.416
from shucking the events of the past

1:12:04.500 --> 1:12:08.666
and buttering itself up
for another great year to come.

1:12:10.375 --> 1:12:11.541
[girl laughing]

1:12:11.625 --> 1:12:15.750
Um, yeah, but I… I thought…
I thought Zach was picking you up?

1:12:15.833 --> 1:12:19.541
[Alex] Fuck. I forgot to tell you.
His dad's making him work the corn maze.

1:12:19.625 --> 1:12:23.125
-Can't you just take the bus?
-Oh shit. Alex, they all just left.

1:12:23.208 --> 1:12:25.333
[Alex] All right, we'll turn around.
We're not far.

1:12:25.416 --> 1:12:27.666
-You good there by yourself?
-Yeah, I'll wait.

1:12:35.208 --> 1:12:36.583
[phone vibrating]

1:12:42.500 --> 1:12:44.500
[ominous music playing]

1:12:56.375 --> 1:12:57.333
[doors open]

1:12:57.416 --> 1:12:59.041
[panting]

1:13:06.500 --> 1:13:07.583
[dialing phone]

1:13:07.666 --> 1:13:10.416
-[line ringing]
-[operator] 911, what's your emergency?

1:13:10.500 --> 1:13:13.958
Yeah, um, I'm at the high school.
My name is Makani Young.

1:13:14.041 --> 1:13:16.333
-[operator] Okay, tell me your emergency.
-[door opens]

1:13:17.375 --> 1:13:20.250
-Makani? Can you tell me what's happening?
-[door closes]

1:13:20.833 --> 1:13:22.250
-[gasps]
-Hello?

1:13:22.333 --> 1:13:23.625
[panting]

1:13:23.708 --> 1:13:25.291
-[screams]
-Whoa, whoa, whoa!

1:13:25.375 --> 1:13:27.166
Makani! It's me! Hey!

1:13:27.250 --> 1:13:30.791
-Caleb. Thank God.
-Um, good to see you too.

1:13:30.875 --> 1:13:33.125
-Everyone's outside. Are you--
-[wet plunging]

1:13:33.208 --> 1:13:34.500
[Makani sighs]

1:13:35.541 --> 1:13:36.625
[gasps]

1:13:45.583 --> 1:13:47.875
[sinister music playing]

1:13:57.791 --> 1:13:59.125
[breathing heavily]

1:14:07.666 --> 1:14:08.875
[door opens]

1:14:08.958 --> 1:14:11.208
[Ollie] Makani!

1:14:21.375 --> 1:14:22.333
You okay?

1:14:27.625 --> 1:14:28.916
[grunting]

1:14:30.750 --> 1:14:31.916
[Ollie] Shh.

1:14:36.333 --> 1:14:37.416
[breathing heavily]

1:14:41.375 --> 1:14:42.708
[Ollie] Hi. Yes.

1:14:42.791 --> 1:14:46.166
We need an ambulance at Osborne High.
Someone's been stabbed.

1:14:46.833 --> 1:14:47.958
In the stomach.

1:14:48.541 --> 1:14:49.458
[Alex] Makani!

1:15:00.833 --> 1:15:02.000
The corn maze.

1:15:05.500 --> 1:15:08.500
["Hot Corn Cold Corn" (Live)
by Flatt & Scruggs playing]

1:15:20.375 --> 1:15:21.708
[indistinct chattering]

1:15:26.458 --> 1:15:28.208
[sinister music playing]

1:15:28.291 --> 1:15:29.708
[liquid splattering]

1:15:40.000 --> 1:15:41.708
-[line ringing]
-Pick up the phone, Zach.

1:15:41.791 --> 1:15:43.958
Thank you. Thank… thank you so much.

1:15:45.000 --> 1:15:46.083
Caleb's okay.

1:15:46.166 --> 1:15:47.125
[sighs]

1:15:47.208 --> 1:15:49.916
Hospital says he's…
he's critical, but he's stable.

1:15:50.875 --> 1:15:52.291
I just hope Zach's okay.

1:15:53.291 --> 1:15:56.958
-Whose farms did his dad buy out?
-[Darby] I mean, pretty much everyone's.

1:15:57.458 --> 1:15:59.875
Jackson's, Macon's.

1:15:59.958 --> 1:16:02.500
Everyone in Osborne
either works for him or hates him.

1:16:02.583 --> 1:16:05.125
-Don't forget Sheriff Adkins.
-What?

1:16:05.208 --> 1:16:07.750
Yeah, the sheriff's broke,
had to sell his land.

1:16:08.333 --> 1:16:11.666
And now Zach's dad's
trying to replace the cops.

1:16:25.666 --> 1:16:27.333
[engine revving]

1:16:28.375 --> 1:16:30.583
I don't even know where to start. I…

1:16:31.708 --> 1:16:35.125
I've been so beyond terrible to you.

1:16:38.833 --> 1:16:39.791
Guys, what is that?

1:16:42.000 --> 1:16:43.750
-Shit.
-[phone ringing]

1:16:43.833 --> 1:16:44.791
[Makani] It's Zach.

1:16:44.875 --> 1:16:46.333
-[Zach] Guys! Hello?
-Zach!

1:16:46.416 --> 1:16:48.458
-Are you okay?
-[Zach] Everything's on fire!

1:16:48.541 --> 1:16:50.291
My dad's inside! I have to find him!

1:16:50.375 --> 1:16:51.500
-What?
-[Zach] Please!

1:16:51.583 --> 1:16:52.583
[phone disconnects]

1:16:53.125 --> 1:16:54.125
What?

1:17:00.166 --> 1:17:02.333
[people screaming]

1:17:21.666 --> 1:17:24.250
Ollie, you said
this car's a piece of shit, right?

1:17:25.000 --> 1:17:27.500
-[laughs]
-Wait, what's the car got to do with it?

1:17:28.458 --> 1:17:29.958
Oh fuck, are you serious?

1:17:30.541 --> 1:17:33.916
We have to try to help. Zach and half
of our class are in that maze right now.

1:17:34.000 --> 1:17:36.083
If we clear a path, they can get out.

1:17:36.166 --> 1:17:38.916
[Alex panting] All right! All right!

1:17:39.833 --> 1:17:41.916
Okay. Let's go save
the goddamn football team!

1:17:42.000 --> 1:17:44.166
[screaming] Oh, shit!

1:17:44.250 --> 1:17:45.208
[engine revving]

1:17:45.291 --> 1:17:46.625
[dramatic music playing]

1:17:52.000 --> 1:17:52.833
[screaming]

1:18:02.083 --> 1:18:03.041
Hey, Jasmine.

1:18:03.125 --> 1:18:04.458
[gasps, screams]

1:18:13.125 --> 1:18:14.666
Shit. Get out! Get out!

1:18:15.708 --> 1:18:16.708
[Alex] Fuck!

1:18:17.791 --> 1:18:19.000
[all panting]

1:18:23.791 --> 1:18:24.833
-What?
-Shit.

1:18:24.916 --> 1:18:25.750
[Alex] Wait, wait!

1:18:30.750 --> 1:18:31.958
[people screaming]

1:18:35.916 --> 1:18:37.208
[panting]

1:18:47.791 --> 1:18:50.375
-Oh my God!
-[indistinct chattering over radio]

1:18:50.458 --> 1:18:52.041
Oh my… oh my God!

1:18:52.125 --> 1:18:53.125
Oh my God!

1:18:53.208 --> 1:18:54.333
[Makani] Zach!

1:18:54.833 --> 1:18:57.000
-[people screaming]
-[Macon] I can't breathe!

1:18:57.083 --> 1:18:58.375
[coughing]

1:18:58.458 --> 1:19:00.708
[Macon] Who's that?
Who's… I can't see shit!

1:19:00.791 --> 1:19:03.041
-Hey.
-[Macon] Wait up for the rest of them!

1:19:03.666 --> 1:19:05.500
Hey! How do we get out of here?

1:19:05.583 --> 1:19:07.208
We got you! We got you! Go! Hurry! Hurry!

1:19:07.291 --> 1:19:09.458
We got you! Go! Yes, we know! We know! Go!

1:19:09.541 --> 1:19:10.750
-Okay, go.
-Get them out.

1:19:10.833 --> 1:19:12.625
-No! We're going with you!
-No, go!

1:19:13.375 --> 1:19:15.166
-You gotta help them!
-Makani.

1:19:16.208 --> 1:19:17.583
We have to go find Zach.

1:19:17.666 --> 1:19:19.791
Go! You know the way out.

1:19:19.875 --> 1:19:21.083
-Help them.
-Come on!

1:19:22.291 --> 1:19:23.375
Zach!

1:19:24.625 --> 1:19:25.958
-[Ollie] Zach!
-[coughing]

1:19:27.916 --> 1:19:29.333
-[Ollie] Shit.
-[Makani] Oh shit!

1:19:29.416 --> 1:19:30.958
[both coughing]

1:19:32.083 --> 1:19:32.916
[Ollie] Zach!

1:19:33.500 --> 1:19:34.583
[Makani] Zach!

1:19:36.708 --> 1:19:40.083
You don't have to do this!
These people have families!

1:19:41.708 --> 1:19:43.416
I have a family!

1:19:44.583 --> 1:19:47.166
-Please!
-[Makani] Hey, asshole!

1:19:54.083 --> 1:19:55.333
[both gasping]

1:19:56.916 --> 1:19:58.041
[choking]

1:19:59.833 --> 1:20:01.375
[sinister music playing]

1:20:13.250 --> 1:20:14.458
Damn it!

1:20:16.666 --> 1:20:17.500
[sighs]

1:20:17.583 --> 1:20:19.083
Do you know how many times--

1:20:22.541 --> 1:20:25.333
Do you know how many times
I've dreamt of that moment?

1:20:25.416 --> 1:20:26.958
[panting] Zach!

1:20:27.041 --> 1:20:29.375
You only get to kill your dad once!

1:20:29.458 --> 1:20:30.625
Jesus.

1:20:30.708 --> 1:20:32.708
I had the perfect thing to say

1:20:34.125 --> 1:20:35.208
to his face.

1:20:37.041 --> 1:20:38.250
What's wrong?

1:20:39.041 --> 1:20:42.583
Second-guessing giving me
The Art of War on my ninth birthday?

1:20:46.666 --> 1:20:48.916
See? Now… now it just sounds stupid.

1:20:49.500 --> 1:20:51.708
He was supposed to be crying and…

1:20:51.791 --> 1:20:55.333
and… and aware of his life choices
and consequences and--

1:20:55.958 --> 1:20:56.875
Fuck!

1:20:56.958 --> 1:20:58.500
Fuckin' sociopath.

1:20:59.375 --> 1:21:00.875
-[clicks]
-Shit.

1:21:01.500 --> 1:21:03.250
No! Oh no!

1:21:03.333 --> 1:21:05.416
I am not a sociopath!

1:21:06.416 --> 1:21:07.500
[gasps]

1:21:07.583 --> 1:21:08.541
[whimpers]

1:21:08.625 --> 1:21:11.125
Does no one know
what that word means anymore?

1:21:11.916 --> 1:21:16.708
If I were a sociopath, I'd have
zero emotional investment in the outcome!

1:21:16.791 --> 1:21:17.625
Ollie!

1:21:17.708 --> 1:21:20.833
This, this is very important to me.

1:21:20.916 --> 1:21:24.708
And… and not to mention
extremely work-intensive.

1:21:24.791 --> 1:21:28.666
Do you know how hard it is
to make these fucking masks?

1:21:28.750 --> 1:21:31.166
[sobbing] Zach, stop, please!
Look, this… this isn't you!

1:21:31.250 --> 1:21:33.416
You have no idea who I am!

1:21:34.000 --> 1:21:35.708
You don't even know who you are!

1:21:36.208 --> 1:21:40.125
I've spent my whole life denying who I am.

1:21:40.208 --> 1:21:43.791
I was ashamed, but why?
Because I was born with privilege?

1:21:43.875 --> 1:21:45.958
Why should I feel bad about that?

1:21:46.708 --> 1:21:49.458
It's not my fault. It's what I was given.

1:21:50.458 --> 1:21:55.166
Do you see now?
You're all wearing masks, Makani Sun-woo.

1:21:55.791 --> 1:21:59.166
You're all putting on
these… these fake faces.

1:21:59.833 --> 1:22:03.208
You're all hypocrites! Just like my dad.

1:22:03.291 --> 1:22:07.458
But I… I can't hide
from my dad's last name.

1:22:08.041 --> 1:22:12.500
So I… I'm… I'm showing
these people who they are!

1:22:12.583 --> 1:22:14.041
Who they really are!

1:22:15.666 --> 1:22:18.500
Take one more fucking step,
and I swear to God, I will--

1:22:18.583 --> 1:22:19.916
What? What?

1:22:20.500 --> 1:22:22.208
You'll push me into the fire?

1:22:22.916 --> 1:22:26.875
Stab me with the same knife you used
on Caleb? On Jackson and Katie?

1:22:27.416 --> 1:22:30.083
The same knife you used
to slit Rodrigo's throat?

1:22:31.083 --> 1:22:33.000
You killed my dad.

1:22:33.083 --> 1:22:34.916
You killed Ollie.

1:22:35.958 --> 1:22:37.791
That's why I had to protect myself

1:22:38.791 --> 1:22:40.208
by killing you.

1:22:40.291 --> 1:22:42.166
[panting]

1:22:42.791 --> 1:22:44.166
But hey, it… it tracks.

1:22:45.166 --> 1:22:47.458
More fire, more victims.

1:22:48.083 --> 1:22:49.458
So you.

1:22:50.416 --> 1:22:52.416
-I mean, cops show up.
-[gasping]

1:22:52.500 --> 1:22:55.750
[Zach] They find the knife,
and they find you dead.

1:22:56.333 --> 1:22:58.208
I could just put this all on you.

1:22:59.375 --> 1:23:01.125
No one would ever know.

1:23:02.041 --> 1:23:03.208
I'll know.

1:23:04.958 --> 1:23:06.041
[grunts]

1:23:08.625 --> 1:23:10.125
-[grunts]
-[Makani panting]

1:23:10.208 --> 1:23:13.166
You think having everything
makes you the victim?

1:23:13.250 --> 1:23:15.750
What kind of fucked-up logic is that?

1:23:15.833 --> 1:23:18.166
Blaming everyone else for what's wrong?

1:23:18.250 --> 1:23:20.541
When you're what's wrong, Zach.

1:23:21.125 --> 1:23:22.666
You're the problem!

1:23:22.750 --> 1:23:24.416
[whimpering]

1:23:24.500 --> 1:23:26.000
Look at me, Zach.

1:23:26.083 --> 1:23:28.166
Look at my face!

1:23:30.750 --> 1:23:33.791
I don't have to wear a mask
to show you who you are.

1:23:33.875 --> 1:23:34.875
[both grunting]

1:23:42.041 --> 1:23:43.708
[gasping]

1:23:52.958 --> 1:23:54.083
Ollie!

1:23:57.791 --> 1:23:58.833
Ollie, no.

1:24:01.708 --> 1:24:03.083
"Hey, Ollie."

1:24:03.666 --> 1:24:05.083
[siren blaring in distance]

1:24:05.166 --> 1:24:06.833
"Hey, Makani."

1:24:08.333 --> 1:24:11.000
I'm so sorry. I'm so sorry.

1:24:12.000 --> 1:24:14.291
Hey, stay with me, Ollie.

1:24:14.375 --> 1:24:15.500
Stay with me.

1:24:16.458 --> 1:24:17.958
Help is coming, okay?

1:24:18.875 --> 1:24:20.083
Stay with me.

1:24:20.166 --> 1:24:21.750
[siren approaching]

1:24:29.041 --> 1:24:30.333
[Makani] "I said,

1:24:31.250 --> 1:24:33.083
'My youth is gone

1:24:34.875 --> 1:24:37.875
Like a fire beaten out by the rain

1:24:40.750 --> 1:24:43.208
That will never sway and sing

1:24:44.666 --> 1:24:46.916
Or play in the wind again'

1:24:49.000 --> 1:24:52.750
I said, 'It is no great sorrow

1:24:52.833 --> 1:24:55.333
That quenched my youth in me

1:24:56.541 --> 1:24:58.500
But only little sorrows

1:24:58.583 --> 1:25:00.208
Beating endlessly'

1:25:03.000 --> 1:25:04.541
I thought my youth was gone

1:25:05.125 --> 1:25:07.125
But all of you returned

1:25:08.875 --> 1:25:11.416
Like a flame at the call of the wind

1:25:12.500 --> 1:25:15.041
It leaped and burned

1:25:16.541 --> 1:25:18.666
Threw off its ashen cloak

1:25:19.625 --> 1:25:21.833
And gowned itself like new

1:25:22.041 --> 1:25:23.125
